<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boldon Saves Strength for 100m Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Ato Boldon of Trinidad slowed his
tempo with 40 meters to go but he was still quick enough to lead the
first semifinal group with a time of 10.00 seconds at the 6th World
Athletics Championships here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old rising star, who shocked the world yesterday in the
second heat with a fabulous time of 9.87, looked left and right three
times during today's race, and seemed very confident to win the world
fastest man title in the final starting two hours later.
</P>
<P>
In the second semifinal, Maurice Green of the United States clocked
9.90 ahead of Donovan Bailey of Canada, 9.91, and Frank Fredericks of
Namibia, 9.93.
</P>
<P>
Bailey, world record holder and Olympic champion, and Green, whose
best time is 9.90, are also gold medal hopefuls in the showdown.
</P>
</TEXT>
