<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dosedel Wins Amsterdam Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Slava Dosedel of Czech
Republic defeated top seed Carlos Moya of Spain to win the
Amsterdam Open tennis tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Dosedel, ranked 59th in the world, clinched the match at 7-6,
7-6, 6-7, 6-2 in three and a half hours.
</P>
<P>
The Czech fell 3-1 behind in the opening set but broke back to
force a tie break which he won 7-4 and went on to take the second,
also in a tie-break.
</P>
<P>
Although the Spaniard recovered to take the third set in
another tie-break, Dosedel dominated the fourth, winning it
comfortably. 
</P>
</TEXT>
