<HEADLINE> Jones Clocks 10.94 Seconds into Women's 100m Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Marion Jones of the United States, the
hot favourite to win the crown of the world fastest woman, hit the
tape in 10.94 seconds in the 100 meters semifinals at the 6th World
Athletics Championships here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
She beat the 37-year-old Merlene Ottey of Jamaice in the same group
and looked a class above the other world class sprinters.
</P>
<P>
Ottey, who never won a gold medal in the 100 meters at the previous
four world championships, started slowly but accelerated fast in the
final stage. The final starts two hours later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
