<HEADLINE> Cattle Struck by Strange Disease in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A strange disease has struck
cattle in Kanchanpur district of far-western Nepal, the official
RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Cattle infected with the disease behave in a strange and crazy
manner, grazing whatever they find and attacking people and other
cattle.
</P>
<P>
The infected cattle die within three days, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Farmers are worried about the disease during the cultivation
season, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
A team of veterinarians have been called from the district
livestock development center to identify the disease, the RSS
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
