<HEADLINE> Go-slow by Air Traffic Controllers Continues in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Air traffic services in three
major airports in Kenya were today still paralyzed following a
go-slow over pay rise by air traffic controllers on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Several airlines, both local and international, were forced to
cancel their flights and travellers were stranded at the airports
in Nairobi, Mombasa and Kisumu.
</P>
<P>
Clearance to land for Arriving flights were delayed for
several hours and some flights were even diverted to neighboring
Tanzania, airport officials said.
</P>
<P>
Air transport services were plunged into complete confusion
after the air traffic controllers downed tools at midnight of
last Friday, three days after their meteorological department
counterparts went on strike.
</P>
<P>
One of the striking controllers said, "our key demand is that
the basic salary of an air controller should be 261,000 Kenyan
Shillings (about 4,300 U.S. Dollars) here in Kenya."
</P>
<P>
"We will continue our strike indefinitely until our demands
are met," he added. 
</P>
