<HEADLINE> Air Crashes Claim 66 Lives in Russia in Jan-June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of victims of air
crashes in Russia totaled 66 in the first half of the year against
35 killed in four air crashes in the same period of 1996, the
Russian Federal Aviation Service reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax cited the service as saying the majority of air
accidents were registered in the southern and central regions of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Federal Aviation Service experts said human error still
accounted for the majority of air accidents, or 79 percent, while
malfunctions in aircraft equipment accounted for 17 percent of air
accidents.
</P>
<P>
In order to increase flight safety, Russia should adopt a
federal law on a state system to ensure the safety of flights of
civil aircraft aimed at raising the role of the state in managing
air transport under new economic conditions, the experts said.
</P>
<P>
The adoption of such a law, they noted, would help stabilize
the level of safety of flights and aviation services within the
next three to four years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
