<HEADLINE> Arabs to Convene Emergency Meeting on Peace Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Permanent delegates to the Arab
League will hold an emergency meeting here Tuesday to adopt a
unified Arab stance on recent Israeli practices against the
Palestinian people, the Egyptian MENA news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The extraordinary session is convened at the request of
Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat, who
accused Israel of picking up a war with the Palestinians by
adopting mass-punitive measures following Wednesday's suicide
bombings in a crowded market in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
PNA permanent delegate to the Arab League Mohamed Sobeih said
today these "arbitrary measures" against the Palestinian people"
are aimed at triggering off violence in the region.
</P>
<P>
"Such provocative measures by Israel are used at times of war
and not peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
The emergency meeting will tackle a ten-item memorandum
submitted by the Palestinian side on the Israeli procedures and a
note from Meguid on the same issue, Sobeih said.
</P>
<P>
Saying the Arab support for the Palestinian rights is a sure
thing, Sobeih called upon the Mideast peace sponsors to bear their
responsibilities in salvaging the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Following the Jerusalem attack which killed 15 people, Israel
immediately imposed a closure on the West Bank and Gaza Strip,
barring tens of thousands of Palestinians from jobs in Israel and
restricting even Palestinians' movements between their autonomous
West Bank towns.
</P>
<P>
It has also closed the Palestinian international
crossing-points with Egypt and Jordan and suspended the transfer
of Palestinian tax and customs revenues to the PNA coffers.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations have been deadlocked since
March when Israel started to build a settlement in East
Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
