<HEADLINE> Turkey Seeks Normalization of Ties With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel today expressed his desire for normalizing relations with
Iran.
</P>
<P>
In his congratulation message to Mohammad Khatami, who was
confirmed as Iran's new president today, Demirel expressed his
belief that maintaining and developing good neighborly relations
are in the national interests of both countries.
</P>
<P>
The Turco-Iranian ties have experienced a bitter period since
February when the two countries expelled diplomats each other.
</P>
<P>
Former Iranian ambassador to Ankara was accused of attending
a controversial religious rally and commending Shariah (Islamic
Law).
</P>
<P>
Turkey also blames Iran for supporting the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party rebels who are termed as the most dangerous
threat to the border security of southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here believe that Khatami, well-known for his
moderate political tendency, will help break the tense situation
between Ankara and Tehran. 
</P>
