<P>
Zhanna Pintussevich of Ukraine was second in 10.85 ahead of
Sevatheda Fynes of Bahamas, 11.03.
</P>
<P>
Jones' winning time is the year's fastest and 0.06 seconds faster
than her personal best.
</P>
<P>
Merlene Ottey of Jamaice, 37, finished a disappointed seventh in
11.29. Bad luck hit Ottey again this time, robbing her perhaps the
last chance to win the world 100m title.
</P>
<P>
The Jamaican sprinting star was twice nipped at the line by Gail
Devers of the United States at the previous meet and last year's
Olympics. After 20 years as a world class dasher, her dream of winning
the crown of the world fastest woman hasn't been fulfilled.
</P>
<P>
In today's final, Sevatheda jumped the gun but Ottey didn't hear
the foul gun. The Olympic silver medallist ran as fast as she could
till 70 meters. The mistake coused her too much power and strength. In
the showdown, when she realised she couldn't get a medal, she just
slowed her pace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
