<HEADLINE> Hussein Urges All to Overcome Crisis Together </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 3 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan here today
called for all the parties concerned to work together in an effort
to overcome the crisis created by the suicide bombings last week
in West Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Hussein made these remarks while receiving a group of Israeli
lawmakers at the Royal Court.
</P>
<P>
The group arrived here earlier today for talks on ways to
reactivate the stalled middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
There was an urgent need to pursue the peace process and
remove all hurdles standing in its way, so it could achieve its
goals, Radio Jordan quoted the king as saying.
</P>
<P>
After the suicide bombings that killed 15 people in an outdoor
market last Wednesday, Israel toughened the security upon the
Palestinian self-rule area, which accelerated the tension in the
region.
</P>
<P>
This has been the newest terrorist violence happening in the
Israeli territories since the peace process was stalled in March
this year due to Israeli government's hardline policy.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, one of the major mediators in the peace process, has
contacted Israel and the United States in an effort to find a
solution for the tension.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed a peace treaty with Israel in 1994. Jordan and
Egypt are the only countries in the Arab world that achieved peace
with the Jewish state. 
</P>
