<HEADLINE> Tanzania Raps Burundi Military Regime for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania today condemned
the military junta of Major Pierre Buyoya for executing five
people in connection with the killings of innocent civilians
after the assassination of civilian President Melchior Ndadaye.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued here by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and
International Cooperation said Tanzania believed that the
military junta has no mandate to hold executions because it was
not democratically-installed.
</P>
<P>
The Statement said the Tanzanian government also believed that
the executions, held last Thursday meant that the military junta
has started killing innocent civilians they thought were hostile
to them.
</P>
<P>
"Tanzania has always been calling for an end of killings in
Burundi so that the planned all-parties peace talks on Burundi
succeed," it said.
</P>
<P>
The government said the act of execution was a manifestation
that military strongman Buyoya wanted to disrupt initiatives by
former President Mwalimu Julius Nyerere, the mediator of the
Burundi crisis.
</P>
<P>
All parties to Burundi's crisis are expected to meet for
negotiations in Arusha, northern Tanzania on August 25, this
year.
</P>
<P>
Apart from disrupting Nyerere's initiatives, the statement
said, the act of execution also hindered efforts by special
envoys to the Burundi crisis.
</P>
<P>
The government has also asked the international community to
condemn the execution by Buyoya which was aimed at strengthening
himself. 
</P>
