<HEADLINE> London Futures Exchange Trades Record July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The London International Financial
Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE), the second largest of its
kind in the world, traded a record of 18.37 million contracts in
July, an increase of 40 percent on July 1996.
</P>
<P>
Average daily volume amounted to 798,696 futures and options
contracts, representing a daily nominal turnover of 172 billion
pounds (283 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Statistics released today show that since the beginning of this
year, LIFFE's cumulative volume has totalled 119.36 million
futures and options contracts, a rise of 24 percent over the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Jack Wigglesworth, chairman of LIFFE, said "LIFFE's volume in
July has been exceptional, reflecting speculation on European
short term interest rates and large movements within the currency
markets."
</P>
<P>
"The continuing growth in contract volumes reflects an
increasing demand by LIFFE's members and end-users for the
Exchange's wide range of products," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
