<HEADLINE> Foreign Banks Operating Well in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign financial institutions
in Shanghai reported significant business growth during the first
six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Shanghai Branch of the People's Bank
of China show a 16.44 percent period rise in the total capital
assets of the city's 44 foreign financial branches, with
outstanding loans and deposits growing by 26.63 percent and 28.57
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Six foreign banks, including CitiBank, the Shanghai and Hong
Kong Banking Corp. and Sanwa Bank of Japan, began handling local
Renminbi business in March this year.
</P>
<P>
End of June figures show that the six foreign banks had
attracted 215 million yuan in deposits and extended 103 million
yuan in loans by the end of June. They also recorded a total
transaction volume of 269 million yuan for interbank lending and
borrowing.  
</P>
