million US dollars), including a 4.8 million US dollar loan from
Australia. The Lhasa Telecommunications Bureau became the region's
first organization to use a foreign loan.
</P>
<P>
"The new system will not only provide local residents with
greater convenience, but will help to improve investment
environment and promote exchanges between Tibet and the
international community," according to a local official. 
