<HEADLINE> Shandong to Strengthen Ties With Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A two-day symposium on
Sino-Japanese relations and ongoing reform and opening efforts in
east China's Shandong Province opened today in Jinan, capital of
the province.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-nine Chinese and Japanese experts attending the
symposium will discuss the great changes in the political,
economic, scientific and cultural fields since the normalization
of Sino-Japanese relations some 25 years ago. They will explore
new approaches for strengthening Shandong's cooperation and
exchanges with Japan.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's Gross Domestic Product has grown by an average 11.9
percent annually for the past decade.
</P>
