<HEADLINE> Russian Ballerina to Make Debut in Beijing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Georgian-born ballerina attempts to continually expand her
talent and knowledge. "One is lost when standing still," said
Ananiashvili, a welcome guest performer for outstanding ballet
companies worldwide, including the Paris Opera Ballet, the Royal
Danish Ballet and New York City Ballet.
</P>
<P>
Ananiashvili has co-starred with Western counterparts in all
well-known modern Western ballet excerpts, an accomplishment quite
rare for ballet dancers from the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very happy to be here," said Ananiashvili. "Members of our
company enjoy performing together and like to make people feel
happy. All members are premier dancers with their respective
companies, a fact which will be discernible during our
performance."
</P>
<P>
Extensive promotional efforts by the National Ballet Troupe of
China (NBTC) and foreign ballet companies have greatly enhanced
the popularity of ballet in China in recent years.
</P>
<P>
According to NBTC director Zhao Ruheng, "The art of ballet has
no boundaries. We think in the same language as foreign dancers."
</P>
<P>
Zhao, China's most famous ballerina, studied under famous
Russian ballet dancers with the Maryinsky Bolshoi in
St. Petersburg. "It's a great honor to watch classical Russian
ballet," said Zhao.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the hope that international exchanges and
cooperation will continue indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
The NBTC and Swedish Royal Ballet jointly sponsored a ballet
performance in May this year and the performance was well received.
</P>
<P>
The International Stars troupe also includes well-known dancers
such as Alexsei Fadeyechev and Yuri Posokhov from the Moscow
Bolshoi, Tatiana Terekhova and Vadim Pisarev with the Kirov
Bolshoi, Inna Dorofeyeva from Deutsche Oper am Rhein, and Marie
Lindqvist and Anders Nordstrom from the Swedish Royal Ballet.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,700 tickets have been sold for tomorrow's performance in
the Beijing Exhibition Center Theater, with the most expensive
tickets priced at 500 yuan each. 
</P>
