<HEADLINE> China Develops New Generation of Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August, 4 (Xinhua) -- The new generation of
domestically manufactured light weapons used to equip the Hong
Kong Garrison of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) will gradually
be distributed throughout the nation's military.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the PLA say the new generation of weapons,
mainly fully automatic rifles and machine guns, equal advance
quality ratings in the world in terms of both performance and
major technical indexes.
</P>
<P>
Chinese-made light weapons, mostly small bore models, are
smaller, lighter, more powerful and have a longer range than
comparable foreign weapons.
</P>
<P>
New materials and techniques were used to develop the new
highly effective multifunctional weapons. The weapons feature
mechanical sighting devices for both day and night firing, and
some models are equipped with grenade launchers. Main parts for
rifles and machine guns are interchangeable.
</P>
<P>
China's highly advanced armaments manufacturing techniques are
also used in the production of numerous other weapons such as
heavy machine guns, snipers rifles and grenade launchers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
