<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Kill Priest In East Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Tamil rebels Sunday
night killed a priest of Hindu Kovil (temple) in Batticaloa town
in Eastern province, an official radio broadcast said this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The priest was murdered by the rebels while performing
religious observances Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The devotees on the premises have identified one rebel who had
come to the Kovil to kill the priest, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
There were about 150 devotees in the Kovil when the rebels
killed the priest.
</P>
<P>
A police team is conducting investigation.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels are fighting for a homeland for minority
Tamils, who account for 18 percent of Sri Lanka's 18.5 million
people. More than 55,000 people have been killed in the civil war
since 1983.  
</P>
