<HEADLINE> S. Africa Expels Portuguese Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Ambassador to
South Africa Vasco Valente has been given 48 hours to leave the
country for leaking a letter from President Nelson Mandela to his
Indonesian counterpart Suharto which was mistakenly delivered to
the Portuguese Embassy.
</P>
<P>
The leaked letter called for the release of jailed East
Timorese rebel leader Xanana Gusmao.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association today quoted unidentified
officials as saying that the 48-hour notice period was given last
week after consultation with the governments of Portugual and
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
It is understood Valente left on Saturday, but it cannot be
confirmed by Portuguese diplomats yet.
</P>
<P>
So far, the South African government declined to make official
comment on the expulsion of Valente.
</P>
<P>
Highly-placed sources here said the expulsion had not soured South
African-Portuguese relations as diplomatic ties had not been
broken. South African Ambassador in Lisbon Kingsley Makubela
would remain in the post while the Portuguese government would
merely replace Valente, they said. 
</P>
