<HEADLINE> South Korea, U.S. to Hold Joint Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 4 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and the United States
will conduct annual military exercises from August 18 to 29,
the South Korean press said today.
</P>
<P>
The routine war games, codenamed Ulchi Focus Lens (UFL), will be
computer-simulated and involve some 16,500 U.S. military personnel
and tens of thousands of South Korean troops.
</P>
<P>
UFL is designed to evaluate and improve combined and joint
coordination, procedures, plans and systems necessary for the
conduct of South Korean and the U.S. government's contingency
operations to defend South Korea, the U.S. military was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The exercises, which have been carried out annually since 1976,
will be conducted at the Combined Forces Command and South Korea's
military installations. 
</P>
