<HEADLINE> Military Attaches Visit PLA Exhibition in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign military attaches based
in Beijing visited the Revolutionary Military Museum today to view
an exhibition of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) modernization
program.
</P>
<P>
The group showed great interest in the numerous pictures,
models and equipment on display.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition featured the latest developments in six areas --
politics, logistics, military proficiency, technology, reserve
forces and foreign relations.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the largest of its kind since the founding of
the People's Republic of China in 1949, is being held to mark the
PLA's 70th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Various members of the group commented favorably on PLA efforts
to open wider to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition highlights the PLA's ties with the armed forces
of over 100 countries, including both developed and developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also tells the viewers that some 1,200 PLA
officers and soldiers have participated in six United Nations
peacekeeping missions in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, jointly sponsored by the Headquarters of the
General Staff, General Political Department and General Logistical
Department of PLA, and the National Defense Science, Technology
and Industry Commission, opened on July 25 and will run through
the end of the year.  
</P>
