<HEADLINE> Australia Not a Racist Country: FM Downer Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Australian Foreign
Minister Alexander Downer reaffirmed here today Australia's
commitment to multi-culturalism and dismissed the Pauline Hanson
controversy as a non-issue.
</P>
<P>
"Australia is not a racist country and it is wrong to form
impression about the country from the remarks of one maverick
politician," he told reporters when asked to comment on Pauline
Hanson's controversial remarks.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the issue was not discussed at all when he
met Singapore leaders today. Describing Miss Hanson as a
non-issue, he said Australia is one of the most tolerant countries
in the world.
</P>
<P>
On his meetings with Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and
Foreign Minister S. Jayakumar, Downer said their two countries
agreed to set up a working committee to prepare the agenda for the
joint ministerial meeting to be held next year. But he declined to
give more details.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
