<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Hits 3.7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Macao in
the second quarter of this year was 3.7 percent, 0.8 percent lower
than in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that the second quarter figure was 0.2 percent higher than
the March-May period.
</P>
<P>
The sub-employment rate stayed at the same level of 0.9 percent
as in the March-May period. The figure for the same quarter last
year stood at 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The highest rate of unemployment was 4.8 percent last year, a
result of a two-year-long slow-down economy, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate began dropping late last year and is expected
to continue this year, with an economic recovery having
shown signs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
