<HEADLINE> Exhibition on ASEAN Facts Opens in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition in commemoration of
the 30th anniversary of the founding of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) was inaugurated at the City Hall
here today.
</P>
<P>
Facts about the nine member countries as well as Cambodia, the
future member, are on show at the week-long exhibition with photos
on socio-economic development of Myanmar, a new ASEAN member
recently admitted into the grouping along with Laos.
</P>
<P>
In addition, documentary video on Myanmar and ASEAN is also
shown with presentation of songs honoring ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Myanmar cultural troupe, made up of noted
musicians and vocalists, has left for Jakarta, Indonesia, to
participate in the ASEAN Song Festival marking the association's
founding anniversary on Thursday under the ASEAN cultural and
information cooperation program.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now embraces nine Southeast Asian countries -- Brunei,
Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand,
Vietnam, Laos and Myanmar.  
</P>
