<HEADLINE> Eriksson Takes Lead in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Kenneth Eriksson took
the lead of the New Zealand Rally from Carlos Sainz of Spain on
the opening stage of the second leg on Monday and remained eight
seconds ahead at the end of the day.
</P>
<P>
As the leading drivers finished the 18th stage and the second
leg, Eriksson in his Subaru Impreza was just ahead of the Ford
Escort of double world champion Sainz and 32 seconds clear of Finn
Juha Kankkunen in a second Ford.
</P>
<P>
Briton Richard Burns remained fourth in his Mitsubishi Carisma,
one minute 31 seconds behind the leaders, after the longest and
toughest leg of the rally.
</P>
<P>
Erkisson, who won two more stages later, gave a huge boost to
the Subaru team after the rertirement on Sunday of former leader
Colin McRae of Britain. 
</P>
