<HEADLINE> Zambia Makes Breakthrough in Fertilizer-Making </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The University of Zambia has made
a breakthrough in manufacturing local fertilizer after more 20
years of research with successful extraction of basal fertilizer
from phospherous rocks.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Fertilizer Technology Development Committee (ZFTDC)
Chairman Glasswell Nkonde said here Sunday that the fertilizer is
reay for mass production if investors are willing to take the
challenge, according to Times of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He said phosphate fertilizers have always been imported at
exorbitant prices and if the mass production of the local
fertilizer is done, the commodity can be sold to people at
reasonable prices.
</P>
<P>
Nkonde said that the fertilizeer has been tested throughout
the country in agriculture research centres and has proved to be
even superior to the imported ones due to the high quality of the
phospherous rocks in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
