<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Claimed Over 1,200 Lives In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,200 people died and 18,000
others injured in road accidents in Zimbabwean last year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launch of the national road traffic safety
awareness week at the weekend, Humphrey Malumo, President of the
Insurance Institute of Zimbabwe said 1,205 people reportedly
died in 38,777 accidents.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that 100 serious accidents occurred in the
country daily.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-five percent of the 38,777 accidents could have been
prevented if road-users had been more careful, he said.
</P>
<P>
Senior Assistant Commissioner of Police Fortune Zenengi
reiterated that road accidents were particularly a problem in
developing countries and were consequently detrimental to the
economy.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwe Republic Police, Zimbabwe Traffic Safety Board,
Vehicle Inspection Department and Automobile Association of
Zimbabwe will jointly focus on encouraging road-users to be
considerate on the roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
