<HEADLINE> Poland Adopts New Environmental Protection Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Polish National Assembly
(parliament) has passed a new environmental protection law, giving
more power to local governments to deal with environmental issues,
according to the Polish Press Agency.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law, all the pollutant enterprises should
strictly hold the pollution level set by the provincial governors,
who are authorized to name the names of the violators.
</P>
<P>
The governors are also empowered to sound alarms when the smoke
level is high in the air and take measures to limit the number of
cars on the street, the report said.
</P>
<P>
However, experts note that although Poland has made great
efforts to improve its environment, it still has a long way to
go. Now, as many as 11 percent of the country are seriously
polluted, with about one third of its population living in the
polluted areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
