<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has launched a
campaign to make the capital city free of visible and invisible
smoke pollution.
</P>
<P>
When formally launching the campaign here today, Environment
Minister Makhdum Mahmood Ahmad said, "The next century will dawn
on Pakistan to find it environmentally clean and concerted efforts
will be made to achieve the objectives."
</P>
<P>
The campaign, which has been planned by the Pakistan
Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) will focus, in its first
phase, on the smoke emissions from the vehicles plying in the
capital city.
</P>
<P>
