<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Cars Go to Lead-Free Petrol in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's gas stations, which
serve China's largest economic center, will offer only lead-free
gas as of October 1.
</P>
<P>
The move is one of the local government's efforts to protect
the urban environment. Motor vehicle's exhaust fumes have become a
major source of pollutants in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai had 744,000 motor vehicles at the end of last
year. Out of 1.1 million tons of petrol the city uses each year,
99 percent contain lead.
</P>
<P>
The municipal environmental protection and traffic management
departments will also install special equipment for motor vehicle
emissions controls, sources say. 
</P>
