<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oldest of Humanity Dies at 122 in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The oldest of humanity, Jeanne
Calment, died today at the age of 122 in Arles, southeast France,
reported Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
Calment was born on February 21, 1875. She married Fernand
Calment in 1896 and they had a daughter in 1898.
</P>
<P>
Until the age 110, she lived all alone in her apartment in
Arles, and joined a medical center for retirees in 1985.
</P>
<P>
The Guiness Book of World Record recognized her in 1993 as the
oldest of humanity.
</P>
<P>
On October 17, 1995, Calment beat the then world record of
longevity by living 120 years and 237 days.
</P>
<P>
AFP said that although blind and deaf, she celebrated each year
her birthday with journalists from around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
