<HEADLINE> Share Prices Down on Singapore Market, But Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Most of the shares fell on the
Singapore market, while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained 8.35 points to close at 1,963.6 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 127.48 million units, worth
340.83 million Singapore dollars. Declines overwhelmed advances by
268 to 67, while 277 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 8.69 million units. Tianjin Zhong Xin had
5.21 million shares traded, while Asia Food &AMP; Properties saw 4.14
million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 70 cents to finish at 28.5 Singapore
dollars. City Developments gained 50 cents to end at 12.9
Singapore dollars. Local food and soft drinks maker F&AMP;N was 40
cents higher at 10.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.3 dollars to end at 29.8 Singapore dollars. Malaya
Cement fell by 70 cents to close at 1.76 dollars, while Bolton and
the Thai Prime Fund finished 40 cents lower at 1.9 Singapore
dollars and 8.65 US dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
