<HEADLINE> USAID Cuts Fund for African Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Agency for International
Development (USAID) has reduced its budget from four million U.S.
Dollars to 820,000 Dollars for funding of development projects in
African countries, an U.S. official said here over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
William Lusasavich, Director of U.S. Information Service, said
countries whose projects were being funded under the USAID
program have been asked to seek new sponsors although this has
put development programs in the region into disarray.
</P>
<P>
The agency had cut its budget funding of all African Credit
Union development programm by 80 percent, said Lusasavich, adding
it had also reduced by 50 percent the number of participating
African countries in development programs.
</P>
<P>
"The cut of funded projects by USAID does not mean the
organisation no longer had any other programs to fund in these
countries. It has undertaken to fund some since it has reduced
its budget by almost three quarters," the U.S. official noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
