<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Moves to Forestall Looming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has released a
initial three billion Kwacha (about 2.3 million U.S.Dollars) to the
Food Reserve Agency (FRA) to buy maize to forestall looming hunger in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail today quoted Deputy Finance Minister Godfrey
Simasiku as saying here on Sunday that one billion Kwacha will be
given on Tuesday this week and the remaining two billion Kwacha late
this month.
</P>
<P>
The three billion Kwacha is part of the 17 billion Kwacha to be
given to FRA to purchase maize.
</P>
<P>
FRA had predicted a maize shortfall of five million bags
(90 kilo per bag) in the country because too much rainfall during the
last agricultural season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
