<HEADLINE> S.Africa to Build 13-Million-Dollar Shopping Mall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A South African corporation will
this month embark on a 13-million-U.S.-Dollar modern shopping
mall in Lusaka, Zambia Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
After its completion, the mall will accommodate over 60
traders and provide full time jobs for about 1,000 people.
</P>
