<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Energy Construction In South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong province's rural
energy development has helped local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Use of methane has been greatly increased, with 160,000
household methane tanks set up by the end of last year, a 13
percent increase over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The province has developed 19 large and medium-sized methane
projects with annual methane production of four million cu.m.,
which produces over 110,000 kwh of electricity.
</P>
<P>
There are also improvements in the use of firewood and coal. By
the end of last year, seven million rural households had rebuilt
stoves. The province has renovated 120,000 ovens, tobacco-curing
ovens, and brickkilns, saving 233,200 tons of standard coal.
</P>
<P>
The rural energy-saving projects have reduced the straw and
firewood use, improving farmland fertilization and preserving
forest resources, contributing a lot to the improvement of rural
environment.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 368 rural energy service companies,
employing 3,700 people, and there is a province-wide rural energy
industrial system for technical advice, help with contracts, and
supplying, installing, and maintenance equipment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
