<HEADLINE> Nearly two Million People Use Drugs in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Nearly two million people in
Russia are using drugs, of whom 300,000 have become addicted, the
Interfax news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
This is due to rampant drug smuggling in the country. Court
cases involving drugs in 1996 numbered five times that of 1990,
sources from the Anti-Drug Bureau of the Interior Ministry was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Russian authorities confiscated more than 50 tons of
drugs and discovered 718 secret drug-processing labs.
</P>
<P>
Drug addiction has led to an increase of HIV carriers at the
speed of 100 people per day, the report said.

