<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urgent: Lebanese Army in Violent Clash with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Israeli airborne commandos
carried out at midnight today an infiltrating attempt in Nabatiyeh
area in south Lebanon and clashed with Lebanese army troops and
Muslim guerrillas, security sources reported this morning.
</P>
<P>
But no confirmation on the involvement of Lebanese army has
been made by government sources.
</P>
<P>
If proved true, this would be the first reported Lebanese
army's involvement in military clashes on the last active
battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict since Israel's "Grapes of
Wrath" operation in south Lebanon in April, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The sources said on condition of anonymity that at 1:00
a.m. (22:00 GMT), several Israeli helicopters landed the commandos
200 meters away from a position of the Lebanese army in the area,
some 75 kilometers southeast of Beirut.
</P>
<P>
During the violent clash, which lasted more than an hour and a
half, the Israeli commandos obtained support from "Apachi"
helicopters taking off from warships cruising in the
Mediterranean water near south Lebanon's coast.
</P>
<P>
The "Apachi" helicopters opened fire at Lebanese army troops
and the guerrillas, and Israeli forces in the hilltop outposts
overlooking the area also fired 155mm and 120mm artilleries toward
the battlefield, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Israeli jet fighters also flied reconnaissance missions at low
altitude over the area when the fighting was going on.
</P>
<P>
At 5:30 a.m. (0230 GMT), Israeli troops detonated the bombs
which they planted during the midnight attack, killing four
guerrillas who were trying to remove them.
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old girl coincidentally passing by was also wounded,
the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
