<HEADLINE> Experts Predict Closer Cooperation Between Hong Kong and Inland Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Weiping, vice-president
of the National Hong Kong and Macao Economic Research Institute,
believes that Hong Kong and the inland area will increase economic
co-operation based on mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
There is competition between Hong Kong and the inland area, he
pointed out, but it should be conducted on an equal basis, and
increased co-operation will not only promote the long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, but will also speed up
economic development of interior provinces.
</P>
<P>
Peng Xiaoyun, a Jinan University professor, noted that Hong
Kong's future is closely tied to China's reforms and
opening-up. She said that much needs to be done in perfecting the
country's economic operations and market economy laws and
regulations.
</P>
<P>
Professor Peng also noted that the gap between Hong Kong and
the interior areas in the economic operations will be narrowed as
economic co-operation increases.  
