<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Death Toll Up to 300 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Tamil rebels death toll has
surpassed 300 since Friday night when they attacked government
troops in Omanthai town, some 220 kilometers north of the capital,
according to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
About 800 rebels of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
with mortars and small arms attacked the manning defenses in
Omanthai town.
</P>
<P>
The government troops successfully retaliated, causing heavy
casualties to the rebels.
</P>
<P>
During the confrontation, more than 300 rebels were killed and
over 200 others injured while 67 troops including two officers
were killed and over 100 wounded, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
LTTE rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war for a separate
Tamil state in the North and East of the country since 1983.
</P>
<P>
The government says more than 50,000 people have been killed in
the war. The LTTE say the toll is higher.  
