<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Govt Appeals Against Acquittal on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh government Sunday
filed an appeal before the High Court against the acquittal of the
accused in the sensational Shima rape and murder case, according
to court sources.
</P>
<P>
Four policemen, accused of raping a garment worker, Shima
Chowdhury, who later died in jail, were acquitted on July 13 by a
Chittagong court, sparking widespread protests.
</P>
<P>
Court sources said Attorney General Barrister Nabi would be
appearing in the case today for admission of the appeal in the
High Court Division of the Supreme Court against the acquittal
order.
</P>
<P>
Shima Chowdhury was allegedly raped by policemen on October 9
last year while under temporary custody and she subsequently died
on February 7 this year in Chittagong Jail where she was kept in
judicial custody.
</P>
<P>
Shima's death in the jail provoked nationwide condemnation and
protest by various organizations, demanding investigation into the
case and punishment to the culprits.
</P>
<P>
It is stated in the petition for appeal that the rape of Shima
was corroborated by medical evidence. However, "since police
investigated the case against police personnel, the investigation
is not maintainable," said the petition.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Parliamentary Committee met Sunday to probe the
death of Shima Chowdhury with committee chairman Foreign Minister
Abdus Samad Azad in the chair.
</P>
<P>
The meeting reviewed a report of the sub-committee which was
submitted earlier to this Parliamentary Committee, according to a
Parliament Secretariat press release.  
</P>
