<HEADLINE> Man Utd Win Charity Shield on Penalties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- League champions Manchester United
won English soccer's season-opening Charity Shield on penalties on
Sunday after being locked at 1-1 with FA Cup winners Chelsea at
the end of the regual time.
</P>
<P>
Both goals came from headers following second half corners.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea striker Mark Hughes nodded Gianfranco Zola's cross down
neatly at the far post in the 52nd minute to put Chelsea ahead but
United defender Ronny Johnsen converted a lofted corner from Ryan
Giggs five minutes later.
</P>
<P>
With the scores level at full time, Chelsea missed two
penalties to give United a 4-2 shoot-out victory.
</P>
<P>
The Charity Shield played at Wembley is the traditional season
curtain-raiser friendly between the league champions and F.A. Cup
winners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
