<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zibo Attracts More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Latest figures show that Zibo, a
city in east China's Shandong Province, has been home to some
1,400 foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The State Council granted Zibo, an inland city with no airport,
approval to open to the outside world in 1988. The city has since
attempted to improve its investment by installing over 300,000
program-controlled telephones, and 17,000 long distance
lines. Zibo has also improved its water and power systems, as well
as various other infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
The UN China Investment Promotions Office under the United
Nation Industrial Development Organization opened its Zibo Work
Station in March this year.
</P>
<P>
Zibo has regulated its industrial structure by channeling over
1.7 billion US dollars in foreign capital into hi-tech industry,
infrastructure facilities and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The city welcomes foreign investment in a wide-range of areas,
including the machinery, electronics, ceramics, textile,
pharmaceuticals and building materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
