<HEADLINE> World Chess Round-robin to Be Held in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 360 players from more
than 20 countries and regions will take part in the 8th World
Chess Round-robin tournament slated from August 3 to 13 in
Koszalin, Poland.
</P>
<P>
Among them are 23 international grandmasters including Colin
McNab of Scotland, Olivier Renet of France, Gilberto Milos of
Brazil, Darryl Johansen of Australia and Mark Tajmanow of Russia.
</P>
<P>
All the 23 grandmasters have scored at least 2500 ranking
points.
</P>
<P>
Winner of the 10-day event will be rewarded with 2,500 pounds
top prize while the runner-up takes 2500 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
