<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woodruff Upsets Kuerten to Win Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Chris Woodruff of the
United States continued his spectacular performance at the
Canadian Open tennis as he upset French Open champion Gustavo
Kuerten of Brazil in Sunday's final to record his first tournament
victory.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Woodruff used aggressive play and a strong
serve to brought down sixth-seeded Kuerten 7-5, 6-4, 6-3 before a
full house of 10,500 at du Maurier Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Woodruff, who was ranked 57th in the world, got to Kuerten in
the final by passing through 16th-seeded Jan Siemerink, No. 2
Goran Ivanisevic, No. 7 Mark Philippoussis and No. 4 Yevgeny
Kafelnikov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
