<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Severe Drought Hits Jinan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Jinan, east China's Shandong Province,
is in the grips of a severe drought resulting from an extended
period of abnormally high temperature.
</P>
<P>
Recent reports indicate water shortages are affecting some 30
percent of the city's total population.
</P>
<P>
The extended heat wave has caused the city's water table to
fall to only 24 meters, a drop of more than three meters on levels
during last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River Water Plant, which normally supplies 200,000
cu.m. of water daily, has been forced to suspend operations due to
low water levels in the lower reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
The city's current 700,000 cu.m daily water supply is some 150,000
cu.m short of the demand.
</P>
<P>
The city, long famous for hundreds of springs, has faced a
critical water shortage since the 1970s, with all local springs
drying up in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The city's water table continues to fall by 5-7 centimeters
daily and there is little hope for rainfall in the foreseeable
future.
</P>
<P>
The local government has introduced measures restricting or
suspending industrial water consumption, and has adopted
contingency plans to limit residential consumption if necessary.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970804.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Toshiba Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland defeated second seed Monica Seles of the United States
by 7-6 (7-4), 6-4 to win the 450,000 U.S. dollars Toshiba Classic
Women's tennis at San Diego, California on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was Hingis' ninth title of the season from her 10 WTA Tour
finals in as many appearances. Her only loss of the year came to
Iva Majoli in the final of the French Open at Roland Garros in
June.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Hingis, who has gained 57-1 overall this year,
including 33-0 on hardcourts, became the youngest Wimbledon winner
in this century last month.
</P>
<P>
Seles, ranked third in the world, advanced to the final on
Saturday with a straight-set victory over Amanda Coetzer of South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
She has compiled a 25-9 record this year, reaching the finals
of four events, but has come up short each time, twice to Hingis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
