<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Thrashes Zimbabwe 11-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Asian teams continue their
victorious record as China followed up Japan's 4-2 win over Canada
to hammer hosts Zimbabwe 11-0 in the field hockey Women's World
Cup group match in Harare.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese took just five minutes to open their account as
Dong Hungkai beat host goalkeeper Nicky Du Toit with a gentle lob.
</P>
<P>
Dong scored her second goal through a penalty stroke and
completed her hat trick in the 69th minute with another lob.
</P>
<P>
Captain Yong Huiping also scored a hat trick for the Chinese
team, which top the group B with four points from one win and one
draw in two outings.
</P>
<P>
In the other two group B matches played on Sunday, Russia beat
Scotland 1-0 while New Zealand downed Spain 3-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
