<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia and Italy Top World Modern Pentathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Italy wrapped up men's
and women's overall team title, respectively, as the Modern
Pentathlon World Championships ended here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Russia finished top in the men's team event with 5,362 points,
followed by United States, Mexico, Poland, Hungary and South
Korea. Hosts Bulgaria only ended up with the 11th place on the
table.
</P>
<P>
Italian women garnered 4,885 points to account for their team
champion, with Poland coming second and Britain the third.
</P>
<P>
Modern Pentathlon Association President Klaus Schormann
concluded the one-week event by praising at Sunday's closing
ceremony that the organization of the competitions was very
outstanding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
