<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Troops Return From Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Nearly half of the Greek troops
participating in the Italian-led multinational security force in
Albania returned home today.
</P>
<P>
The Greek contigent, 278 officers and non-commissioned
officers, arrived in the northern Greek port of Thessaloniki this
morning.
</P>
<P>
Greek Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos said at a welcoming
ceremony that the presence and initiatives of the Greek force made
it possible for the Albanians to hold free and democratic
elections and thus opened the way for Greek armed forces to assume
a role of "ambassador of peace" in countries faced with long
crises, instability and abnormity.
</P>
<P>
In April, a total of more than 700 Greek troops arrived in the
neighboring country to protect the speedy distribution of
humanitarian aid and the June 29 general elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
