<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Takes Delivery of US-Made Missile Launchers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Greece today took delivery of the
last nine U.S.-made MLRS missile launchers.
</P>
<P>
According to a contract between Greece and the United States
signed in 1995, Greece could obtain 18 MLRS missile launchers from
the United States with a total cost of 27 billion drachmas (about
9.3 million U.S. dollars). The first nine such missile launchers
arrived in Greece in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The mobile launchers are reportedly based on all-terrain
vehicles and feature fully automated launching procedures.
</P>
<P>
They can launch 12 missiles simultaneously with a range of 32
kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
